# TV Show Tracker - Full Stack Challenge

## Author: Miguel Pintado

## Overview
This project is a **full-stack TV show tracker** built with a **.NET 8 Web API backend** and a **React JS frontend**.  
Allows users to register, log in, browse TV shows, and manage their list of favorites. 

This solution implements a full-stack TV show tracker using **.NET 8** for the backend and **React (Vite)** for the frontend.  
The backend follows an architecture with services, controllers, and dependency injection.
Uses **Entity Framework Core**, and **JWT** for secure authentication and data persistence.  
It exposes **REST APIs** for user registration, login, show listing, and favorites management.  
The frontend, built with **React**, **React Router**, and **Material UI**.  
**CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing)** is configured to allow safe communication between frontend and backend.
The app supports user authentication, show browsing, and favorites tracking features. 

